    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Technique using a silver wire or rod to draw on a prepared surface, usually paper or parchment; when a silver mark is made on the ground, the metal particles tarnish to form a black mark of silver sulfide. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
